title: Weather Adjusts High School Football Games
text:
Weather Adjusts High School Football Games Tools 
Story Created: Oct 1, 2015 at 4:16 PM EDT Story Updated: Oct 1, 2015 at 4:16 PM EDT Weather has caused some adjustments to the week six high school football schedule in the Midlands. The below games were originally scheduled for Friday and will now be played Thursday night at 7:30 (unless otherwise noted).New Thursday gamesGreat Falls at C.A. Johnson (Bolden Stadium) 7 p.m.Lugoff-Elgin at Lexington
